00:00:08.300 --> 00:00:10.067 position:35% line:83% align:start
[detective]
 <i>The victim's entire head</i>

00:00:10.100 --> 00:00:12.367 position:24% line:83% align:start
had been smashed in
by a blunt object.

00:00:12.400 --> 00:00:14.834 position:24% line:83% align:start
It was so bad that
we couldn't identify

00:00:14.868 --> 00:00:17.300 position:27% line:83% align:start
his face or match
any dental records.

00:00:17.334 --> 00:00:18.968 position:27% line:83% align:start
but we're certain
that the victim

00:00:19.000 --> 00:00:21.367 position:7% line:89% align:start
is Sergeant Tokunosuke Terada.

00:00:21.400 --> 00:00:23.167 position:24% line:83% align:start
We're still unsure
why Detective Terada

00:00:23.200 --> 00:00:25.901 position:21% line:83% align:start
went to an abandoned
gas station by himself

00:00:25.934 --> 00:00:27.634 position:13% line:89% align:start
in the middle of the night.

00:00:27.667 --> 00:00:28.834 position:27% line:89% align:start
On his cellphone,

00:00:28.868 --> 00:00:30.901 position:19% line:83% align:start
we found some personal
text messages

00:00:30.934 --> 00:00:32.968 position:27% line:83% align:start
exchanged between
the two of you.

00:00:33.000 --> 00:00:35.200 position:33% line:83% align:start
The estimated
time of death was today,

00:00:35.234 --> 00:00:37.968 position:27% line:83% align:start
between the hours
of 2:00 and 3:00 AM.

00:00:38.000 --> 00:00:41.000 position:30% line:83% align:start
Where were you,
and what were you doing?

00:00:43.133 --> 00:00:45.367 position:13% line:89% align:start
[Saki] I was at home alone.

00:00:55.834 --> 00:00:59.167 position:30% line:89% align:start
[opening music]

00:02:15.367 --> 00:02:17.167 position:19% line:83% align:start
[reporter] <i>The body of</i>
 <i>a man thought to be an officer</i>

00:02:17.200 --> 00:02:19.501 position:19% line:83% align:start
of the Makurazaka City
Police Department

00:02:19.534 --> 00:02:20.601 position:16% line:89% align:start
was found around 6:00 AM.

00:02:20.634 --> 00:02:23.267 position:13% line:83% align:start
It was reported that a body
with its face smashed in

00:02:23.300 --> 00:02:24.834 position:16% line:83% align:start
was found at an abandoned
gas station along the freeway.

00:02:24.868 --> 00:02:26.367 position:35% line:83% align:start
[reporter]
 <i>And although there's</i>

00:02:26.400 --> 00:02:28.067 position:13% line:83% align:start
- <i>no official statement...</i>
-[Chief] You okay?

00:02:28.100 --> 00:02:29.534 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>-from the police department</i>
 <i>at this time, we will</i>

00:02:29.567 --> 00:02:31.834 position:10% line:83% align:start
-c <i>ontinue to update you</i> ...
-[Saki] Chief! I...

00:02:31.868 --> 00:02:34.100 position:38% line:83% align:start
Yes sir,
though a little stunned.

00:02:34.133 --> 00:02:36.267 position:19% line:83% align:start
Detective Terada seemed
really happy lately

00:02:36.300 --> 00:02:38.334 position:10% line:83% align:start
because he was hitting it off
with you.

00:02:40.834 --> 00:02:42.100 position:16% line:83% align:start
There's a high likelihood
he was killed

00:02:42.133 --> 00:02:44.534 position:16% line:83% align:start
due to a grudge incurred
on the job.

00:02:44.567 --> 00:02:45.501 position:24% line:89% align:start
Suffice it to say,

00:02:45.534 --> 00:02:47.000 position:30% line:83% align:start
other officers
are being questioned

00:02:47.033 --> 00:02:48.934 position:16% line:83% align:start
about their interactions
with Detective Terada,

00:02:48.968 --> 00:02:50.267 position:27% line:89% align:start
just as you were.

00:02:50.300 --> 00:02:52.734 position:13% line:83% align:start
The Makurazaka Police Dept.
staff are the ones

00:02:52.767 --> 00:02:54.834 position:19% line:89% align:start
being questioned first.

00:02:54.868 --> 00:02:56.968 position:19% line:89% align:start
By the way, Yumihara...

00:02:57.000 --> 00:02:58.501 position:30% line:83% align:start
Is it true that
Detective Terada

00:02:58.534 --> 00:03:00.367 position:27% line:83% align:start
was investigating
Steel Lady Nanase?

00:03:00.400 --> 00:03:03.501 position:24% line:83% align:start
Yes. I mentioned it
during my interrogation,

00:03:03.534 --> 00:03:04.667 position:27% line:89% align:start
when I was asked.

00:03:04.701 --> 00:03:07.167 position:13% line:83% align:start
The investigating detective
already knew...

00:03:07.200 --> 00:03:09.701 position:13% line:83% align:start
Wait, has the media gotten
that info?

00:03:09.734 --> 00:03:11.367 position:7% line:89% align:start
No, it hasn't been leaked yet.

00:03:11.400 --> 00:03:13.234 position:10% line:83% align:start
But there are people who are
trying to connect

00:03:13.267 --> 00:03:14.834 position:33% line:83% align:start
the incident
with Detective Terada

00:03:14.868 --> 00:03:16.367 position:19% line:89% align:start
to Steel Lady Nanase...

00:03:16.400 --> 00:03:19.968 position:10% line:83% align:start
since his face was smashed in
during a late night encounter.

00:03:20.000 --> 00:03:21.834 position:35% line:83% align:start
Apparently,
that's making some people

00:03:21.868 --> 00:03:24.067 position:30% line:83% align:start
believe it was
Steel Lady Nanase.

00:03:24.100 --> 00:03:25.834 position:19% line:89% align:start
Talk about a sick joke.

00:03:25.868 --> 00:03:28.133 position:27% line:83% align:start
Yes. It is quite
irresponsible...

00:03:28.167 --> 00:03:31.100 position:19% line:83% align:start
Inventing rumors about
somebody's death like that.

00:03:31.133 --> 00:03:32.534 position:19% line:83% align:start
I just have a hard time
believing that

00:03:32.567 --> 00:03:35.501 position:7% line:83% align:start
Detective Terada of all people,
was beaten to death.

00:03:35.534 --> 00:03:38.701 position:30% line:83% align:start
What could have
possibly happened?

00:03:38.734 --> 00:03:40.100 position:35% line:89% align:start
If only...

00:03:40.133 --> 00:03:43.200 position:24% line:83% align:start
If only I would've
been more reliable...

00:03:43.234 --> 00:03:45.868 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>I should've done</i>
 <i>a better job warning him...</i>

00:03:45.901 --> 00:03:47.734 position:19% line:83% align:start
This isn't your fault,
Yumihara.

00:03:47.767 --> 00:03:50.400 position:10% line:89% align:start
But still, it feels like I...

00:03:50.434 --> 00:03:52.267 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>Of course,</i>
 <i>there's no trace of a fight,</i>

00:03:52.300 --> 00:03:55.267 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>or of him struggling,</i>
 <i>or of the suspect...</i>

00:03:55.300 --> 00:03:59.267 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>Because he was killed</i>
 <i>by Steel Lady Nanase.</i>

00:03:59.300 --> 00:04:02.267 position:13% line:83% align:start
I can't help but feel that
I was too cold to him.

00:04:02.300 --> 00:04:04.267 position:35% line:83% align:start
After all,
I had only just recently

00:04:04.300 --> 00:04:06.067 position:19% line:89% align:start
learned his first name.

00:04:06.100 --> 00:04:07.234 position:19% line:89% align:start
That's not your fault.

00:04:07.267 --> 00:04:09.534 position:19% line:83% align:start
Detective Terada hated
that name.

00:04:09.567 --> 00:04:11.767 position:10% line:83% align:start
Said it was too old-fashioned
and meek.

00:04:11.801 --> 00:04:13.734 position:16% line:89% align:start
He hated being called it.

00:04:13.767 --> 00:04:15.501 position:13% line:89% align:start
Most people never knew it.

00:04:17.033 --> 00:04:19.400 position:21% line:89% align:start
[cell phone buzzing]

00:04:21.267 --> 00:04:23.601 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>The police won't be able</i>
 <i>to capture the real culprit...</i>

00:04:23.634 --> 00:04:26.300 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>Neither Steel Lady Nanase</i>
 <i>nor the imaginations</i>

00:04:26.334 --> 00:04:29.334 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>of the people</i>
 <i>that created her.</i>

00:04:29.367 --> 00:04:31.501 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>The case will likely</i>
 <i>go unsolved.</i>

00:04:31.534 --> 00:04:34.133 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>The only ones who can defeat</i>
 <i>that monster</i>

00:04:34.167 --> 00:04:35.901 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>are those who know</i>
 <i>the truth and</i>

00:04:35.934 --> 00:04:38.334 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>have the power to</i>
 <i>do something about it.</i>

00:04:40.501 --> 00:04:42.367 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Kotoko] <i>Right after</i>
 <i>the news this morning,</i>

00:04:42.400 --> 00:04:44.334 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>the internet went wild</i>
 <i>with the story</i>

00:04:44.367 --> 00:04:46.734 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>that Steel Lady Nanase had</i>
 <i>finally killed someone</i>

00:04:46.767 --> 00:04:48.234 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>and a cop at that.</i>

00:04:48.267 --> 00:04:50.968 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Even a few TV personalities</i>
 <i>are saying this death</i>

00:04:51.000 --> 00:04:52.968 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>is connected with</i>
 <i>Karin Nanase's.</i>

00:04:53.000 --> 00:04:54.467 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>This went</i>
 <i>national instantly.</i>

00:04:54.501 --> 00:04:58.100 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>The posts have been</i>
 <i>multiplying exponentially.</i>

00:05:06.367 --> 00:05:07.334 position:35% line:89% align:start
 <i>I'm tired.</i>

00:05:07.367 --> 00:05:10.133 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>I can't remember</i>
 <i>the last time it rained...</i>

00:05:10.167 --> 00:05:13.234 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I miss the comfort of</i>
 <i>the bench at the hospital.</i>

00:05:13.267 --> 00:05:16.701 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>It was so quiet,</i>
 <i>yet so freeing.</i>

00:05:16.734 --> 00:05:18.200 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>I want to drift</i>
 <i>to sleep there,</i>

00:05:18.234 --> 00:05:21.400 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>as I listen to the sound</i>
 <i>of the falling rain.</i>

00:05:21.434 --> 00:05:26.567 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>It'd be even better if</i>
 <i>Kuro was right by my side.</i>

00:05:26.601 --> 00:05:27.467 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Kuro] Iwanaga.

00:05:27.501 --> 00:05:28.334 position:30% line:89% align:start
[Kotoko gasps]

00:05:33.567 --> 00:05:34.467 position:27% line:89% align:start
Time for a break.

00:05:36.534 --> 00:05:37.634 position:35% line:89% align:start
Have some.

00:05:37.667 --> 00:05:39.133 position:16% line:89% align:start
Keep your blood sugar up.

00:05:41.934 --> 00:05:43.200 position:19% line:89% align:start
It's a bit lackluster.

00:05:43.234 --> 00:05:44.901 position:30% line:83% align:start
Just enough to
make me hungry.

00:05:44.934 --> 00:05:47.868 position:7% line:83% align:start
That's what you say after being
given high-quality chocolates?

00:05:47.901 --> 00:05:49.267 position:24% line:89% align:start
That snark is rich

00:05:49.300 --> 00:05:51.701 position:10% line:83% align:start
from the person who's staying
at the same hotel as me,

00:05:51.734 --> 00:05:52.968 position:16% line:89% align:start
yet got a separate room.

00:05:53.000 --> 00:05:54.901 position:16% line:83% align:start
Aren't you supposed to be
my boyfriend?

00:05:54.934 --> 00:05:56.167 position:16% line:89% align:start
Look, I did that because

00:05:56.200 --> 00:05:59.067 position:16% line:83% align:start
I wanted you to get some
actual sleep, okay?

00:05:59.100 --> 00:06:01.367 position:24% line:83% align:start
How about you don't
let me sleep?

00:06:01.400 --> 00:06:04.367 position:10% line:83% align:start
"Early to bed, early to rise"
is the key to good health.

00:06:04.400 --> 00:06:07.400 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Did an immortal just try to</i>
 <i>talk to me about health?</i>

00:06:07.434 --> 00:06:08.133 position:35% line:89% align:start
What's up?

00:06:08.167 --> 00:06:09.634 position:19% line:89% align:start
Nothing, just thinking.

00:06:09.667 --> 00:06:12.834 position:7% line:83% align:start
Have you made any progress with
your research on the wiki?

00:06:12.868 --> 00:06:14.901 position:13% line:83% align:start
Well things have definitely
taken a turn

00:06:14.934 --> 00:06:16.300 position:24% line:83% align:start
since the incident
this morning.

00:06:16.334 --> 00:06:18.234 position:21% line:83% align:start
The vast majority of
the comments section

00:06:18.267 --> 00:06:21.234 position:21% line:83% align:start
believes that this is
the work of Steel Lady Nanase.

00:06:21.267 --> 00:06:23.367 position:19% line:83% align:start
If you do a search for
the victim's name,

00:06:23.400 --> 00:06:26.968 position:10% line:83% align:start
you can see that he was even
an Olympic candidate in judo.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:29.100 position:21% line:83% align:start
But someone like him
being beaten to death,

00:06:29.133 --> 00:06:30.968 position:7% line:89% align:start
with no signs of a struggle...

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:33.033 position:24% line:83% align:start
Sounds so bizaare,
it's easy to think

00:06:33.067 --> 00:06:35.100 position:10% line:89% align:start
Steel Lady Nanase's to blame.

00:06:35.133 --> 00:06:37.234 position:19% line:83% align:start
People are spouting off
theories and rumors

00:06:37.267 --> 00:06:39.534 position:10% line:83% align:start
concerning Detective Terada's
death, then

00:06:39.567 --> 00:06:42.701 position:7% line:83% align:start
there's the net creeps going on
about Karin Nanase's boobs.

00:06:42.734 --> 00:06:44.033 position:13% line:89% align:start
That makes a lot of sense.

00:06:44.067 --> 00:06:46.801 position:33% line:83% align:start
Her chest was
incredibly bouncy.

00:06:46.834 --> 00:06:48.100 position:13% line:89% align:start
What, did you touch them?!

00:06:48.133 --> 00:06:49.300 position:27% line:83% align:start
Or did you try to
squeeze them

00:06:49.334 --> 00:06:50.934 position:33% line:83% align:start
when you were
holding on to her?!

00:06:50.968 --> 00:06:52.634 position:10% line:83% align:start
I wasn't thinking about that
at the time.

00:06:52.667 --> 00:06:55.033 position:16% line:83% align:start
You definitely could have
if you chose a future

00:06:55.067 --> 00:06:56.601 position:7% line:89% align:start
where you brushed against them!

00:06:56.634 --> 00:06:58.100 position:16% line:89% align:start
You had the opportunity!

00:06:58.133 --> 00:06:59.801 position:24% line:83% align:start
If I cared so much
about big boobs,

00:06:59.834 --> 00:07:01.667 position:19% line:83% align:start
I never would've dated
you or Saki.

00:07:01.701 --> 00:07:03.968 position:16% line:83% align:start
You may have yearned for
something different...

00:07:04.000 --> 00:07:06.100 position:19% line:83% align:start
Just once in your life,
you might've wanted to

00:07:06.133 --> 00:07:09.501 position:10% line:83% align:start
manhandle those exceptionally
choice mounds of fat!

00:07:09.534 --> 00:07:12.167 position:13% line:83% align:start
Can you swear to Amaterasu
that you didn't have

00:07:12.200 --> 00:07:14.367 position:16% line:83% align:start
such pervy thoughts cross
your dirty mind?!

00:07:14.400 --> 00:07:17.467 position:16% line:83% align:start
This is starting to sound
like you're projecting...

00:07:17.501 --> 00:07:18.367 position:41% line:89% align:start
[groan]

00:07:19.267 --> 00:07:20.701 position:16% line:89% align:start
Let's get back on topic.

00:07:20.734 --> 00:07:21.868 position:30% line:89% align:start
At this point,

00:07:21.901 --> 00:07:23.167 position:21% line:83% align:start
it's hard to dismiss
Steel Lady Nanase

00:07:23.200 --> 00:07:25.133 position:13% line:83% align:start
as being nothing more than
a mere rumor.

00:07:25.167 --> 00:07:27.901 position:10% line:83% align:start
People are now more inclined
to believe it was a ghost.

00:07:27.934 --> 00:07:30.067 position:16% line:83% align:start
It was already happening
before now.

00:07:30.100 --> 00:07:32.934 position:16% line:83% align:start
Ever since the rumors of
Steel Lady Nanase began,

00:07:32.968 --> 00:07:35.234 position:19% line:83% align:start
the idea that this was
a ghost, and that

00:07:35.267 --> 00:07:38.901 position:19% line:83% align:start
it was harassing people
were well received.

00:07:38.934 --> 00:07:42.234 position:7% line:83% align:start
The scales are tipping too far
toward one side.

00:07:42.267 --> 00:07:44.300 position:21% line:83% align:start
Look, Kuro I'm going
to be blunt.

00:07:44.334 --> 00:07:45.601 position:41% line:89% align:start
Go on.

00:07:45.634 --> 00:07:49.234 position:10% line:83% align:start
I think that Rikka is heavily
intertwined with this case.

00:07:49.267 --> 00:07:52.067 position:27% line:83% align:start
In truth, I think
she's at its core.

00:07:53.667 --> 00:07:54.934 position:33% line:89% align:start
I knew that,

00:07:54.968 --> 00:07:58.000 position:19% line:83% align:start
but I can't defend her
now that someone's dead.

00:08:04.934 --> 00:08:06.334 position:21% line:83% align:start
-[knock on the door]
-[Kotoko surprised]

00:08:22.801 --> 00:08:24.067 position:41% line:89% align:start
[creak]

00:08:24.100 --> 00:08:25.834 position:13% line:89% align:start
I'm sorry for running late.

00:08:25.868 --> 00:08:27.868 position:24% line:89% align:start
Are you okay, Saki?

00:08:27.901 --> 00:08:29.601 position:21% line:89% align:start
I'm fine. Thank you.

00:08:32.133 --> 00:08:33.701 position:13% line:89% align:start
There's no doubt, is there?

00:08:33.734 --> 00:08:36.367 position:21% line:83% align:start
The Steel Lady caused
Detective Terada's death.

00:08:36.400 --> 00:08:37.434 position:27% line:89% align:start
[Kotoko] Correct.

00:08:37.467 --> 00:08:39.234 position:21% line:83% align:start
[Kotoko] An ayakashi
who saw the incident

00:08:39.267 --> 00:08:41.801 position:10% line:83% align:start
as it happened came to see me
this morning.

00:08:41.834 --> 00:08:43.901 position:35% line:83% align:start
He gave me
an eyewitness account.

00:08:43.934 --> 00:08:45.133 position:33% line:89% align:start
[Saki] I see.

00:08:45.167 --> 00:08:47.367 position:10% line:83% align:start
This may be a stupid question
to ask,

00:08:47.400 --> 00:08:49.534 position:10% line:83% align:start
but will Detective Terada now
be a ghost

00:08:49.567 --> 00:08:50.567 position:21% line:89% align:start
wandering this world?

00:08:50.601 --> 00:08:52.968 position:16% line:83% align:start
Well, it's not as though
everybody who dies

00:08:53.000 --> 00:08:54.701 position:21% line:83% align:start
just becomes a ghost,
and roams.

00:08:54.734 --> 00:08:56.167 position:30% line:83% align:start
If he doesn't,
that's preferred.

00:08:56.200 --> 00:08:58.400 position:19% line:83% align:start
They're better off not
being left to wander.

00:08:58.434 --> 00:09:02.634 position:16% line:83% align:start
Of course. I guess it was
a stupid question.

00:09:02.667 --> 00:09:03.801 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:09:03.834 --> 00:09:05.968 position:10% line:89% align:start
Regardless, this isn't good.

00:09:06.000 --> 00:09:08.100 position:19% line:83% align:start
True. We would've been
far better off

00:09:08.133 --> 00:09:11.267 position:16% line:83% align:start
if the culprit was anyone
other than Steel Lady Nanase.

00:09:11.300 --> 00:09:13.100 position:13% line:83% align:start
They say the victim's face
was smashed in!

00:09:13.133 --> 00:09:14.634 position:7% line:89% align:start
[internet user] Could it be...?

00:09:14.667 --> 00:09:16.868 position:13% line:83% align:start
[Kotoko] While people were
stirring over the fact

00:09:16.901 --> 00:09:18.734 position:19% line:83% align:start
